Mus musculus: A custom perspective for use with adult kidney images produced by GenePaint for the EuReGene project.  Brigitte Kaissling uses this in Fiatas to annotate such images.  This is a highly idiosyncratic perspective and should not be used for any other purpose.  The whole need for this perspective may go away when we split TS28 into juvinile and adult.
Renal/Urinary subset of the mouse anatomy ontology.
Reproductive and Renal/Urinary subset of the mouse anatomy ontology.

mouse: The Anatomical Basis of Mouse Development

EMAPT:: Version created from CIOF file exported by GUDMAP version of EMAP.

Revision of the GUDMAP/EuReGene anatomy.  This is the first version that was created by revsing the previous database in place, rather than replacing it entirely.  This is the first version that logs changes.

Third revision of GUDMAP/EuReGene anatomy database.  Includes a great deal of changes in the urogenital parts of the anatomy, non-alphabetical sibling term ordering, and deletes many timed nodes that should have been deleted in earlier revisions.
Version 4 of GUDMAP/EuReGene anatomy database.  Includes a great deal of changes in the urogenital parts of the anatomy.  It also includes minor changes to the schema to accommodate Xenopus anatomy.
